n: Teacher Education beyond Minority-Serving Institutions -- tNotes on Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe first of its kind, Teacher Education across Minority-Serving Institutions brings together innovative work from the family of institutions known as minority-serving institutions: Historically Black Colleges and Universities, Tribal Colleges and Universities, Hispanic Serving Institutions, and Asian American and Native American Pacific Islander Serving Institutions. The book moves beyond a singular focus on teacher racial diversity that has characterized scholarship and policy work in this area. Instead, it pushes for scholars to consider that racial diversity in teacher education is not simply an end in itself but is, a means to accomplish other goals, such as developing justice-oriented and asset-based pedagogies.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jan 2021) 0aMinority teachersxTraining ofzUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aDaoud, Annette M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBay, Mary1 aHarper, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrinkerhoff, Jonathan1 aBrowning, Sandra1 aSeo, Byung-In, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamb, Carmelita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaplin, Mae S.1 aTorrez, Cheryl A. Franklin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLansing, Danielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaoud, Annette M.1 aMclurkin, Denise L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, Dewitt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetch